text: Getting my pup to even press the buttons at first was challenging. We had to work on targeting for a bit, first getting her to poke specific things with her nose, then with her paw. We only have one button right now for "outside" and she has to click it before we go out. The issue right now is that she doesn't seem to click it unprompted. She knows that we won't take her out unless it's clicked, so we don't have to command, but she won't go near the door/button unless a human is already standing near the door.
